# Blog Post Creation Guide

When creating a new blog post, follow this structure:

## File Structure

Create a new directory in `src/app/blog/[slug]/` where `[slug]` is a kebab-case URL-friendly name (e.g., `my-new-blog-post`).

Each blog post requires two files:

### 1. `page.tsx`
A simple wrapper that imports and renders the content:

```tsx
import Content from "./content.mdx";

export default function Page() {
  return <Content />;
}
```

### 2. `content.mdx`
The actual blog content file with this structure:

```tsx
import { BlogLayout } from "@/components/BlogLayout";

export const meta = {
  date: "YYYY-MM-DD", // Format: YYYY-MM-DD
  title: "Your Blog Post Title",
};

export default (props) => <BlogLayout meta={meta} {...props} />;

## Your Markdown Content Here

Write your blog post content in markdown below the default export.
```

## Important Notes

- The blog post will be automatically discovered by `getAllBlogs()` which looks for `*.mdx` or `*/content.mdx` files
- Blogs are sorted by date (newest first)
- Use kebab-case for the folder/slug name
- Date format must be `YYYY-MM-DD`
- The title in the meta object will be used for display
- You can use markdown, images, and MDX components in the content
- Images should be placed in `public/images/` and referenced with paths like `/images/your-image.png`
- Keep the tone humble and avoid overly boastful language

## Example

For a blog post about "My Journey Learning TypeScript", create:
- `src/app/blog/my-journey-learning-typescript/page.tsx`
- `src/app/blog/my-journey-learning-typescript/content.mdx`
